Egypt Stocks: Alexandria Portland, EFG-Hermes, Orascom Telecom

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-03-30T11:24:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/egypt-stocks-alexandria-portland-efg-hermes-orascom-telecom.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
gained for a fourth day, rising 1.5 percent to 5,488.55 at 12:48
p.m. in Cairo. The measure has retreated 23 percent this
quarter, the world’s worst performer.  The following stocks rose or fell in Egypt. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Alexandria Portland Cement Co. (ALEX EY) rose 5.1 percent
to 18.11 Egyptian pounds, heading for its highest close since
Jan. 17. The nation’s third-biggest publicly traded cement
manufacturer said profit gained 17 percent to 590 million pounds
($99 million) last year.  EFG-Hermes Holding SAE (HRHO EY) advanced 4 percent to 22
pounds, poised for its largest daily gain since May. Egypt’s
biggest publicly traded investment bank said profit gained 27
percent to 700.8 million Egyptian pounds in 2010.  Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE)   fell 2.5 percent to
4.32 pounds, headed for its biggest daily loss in a week. North
Africa’s biggest publicly traded mobile network operator is in
talks with  Zimbabwe ’s government to reduce its stake in local
unit, Telecel, to 49 percent from 60 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
